easydox Introduction

library(easydox)

Introduction

In most of the functions, the function paramaters follow the pattern of y~x1+x2+x3, dataset, color, facet. The function details can be check typing ?[function_name] in the R Console.

An example using dataset Towels2

A box plot to check the equal variances assumption in ANOVA

dox_boxplot(LogStrength ~ Brand, Towels2, color = Water)

dox_boxplot(LogStrength ~ Brand, Towels2, facet = Water)

dox_boxplot(LogStrength ~ Brand, Towels2, facet = Brand~Water)

A scatterplot to check the equal variances assumption in ANOVA

dox_scatterplot(LogStrength ~ Brand, Towels2, color = Water)

dox_scatterplot(LogStrength ~ Brand, Towels2, color = Water, jitter = 0.05)

dox_scatterplot(LogStrength ~ Brand, Towels2, facet = Water, jitter = 0.15)

An interactive table to show standard deviations of different groups

dox_table(LogStrength ~ Brand + Water, Towels2)

You can sort the GroupVariance or other columns by clicking the column name.

Summary Statistics to Check Missing Data or Balanced Design

dox_sumstats(LogStrength ~ Brand + Water, Towels2)
#>    Brand.Water      min       Q1   median       Q3      max     mean         sd  n missing

IID and Normality Assumption Checking

dox_resid(LogStrength~Brand*Water, Towels2)

dox_resid(LogStrength~Brand*Water, Towels2, plot = 2, bins = 40)

Main Effect Plots

dox_main(LogStrength ~ Brand + Water, Towels2, label="Mean", text_size = 14)

If you are only interested in one treatment (or you have a 3-way ANOVA), you can simply add (or reduce) parameters in the function inputs.

dox_main(LogStrength ~ Brand + Water, Towels2, label="Effect", text_size = 14)

Interaction Effect Plot

dox_inter(LogStrength ~ Water + Brand, Towels2, label="Mean",text_size = 14)

dox_inter(LogStrength ~ Water + Brand, Towels2, label="Effect", text_size = 14)

ANOVA Table

dox_aov(LogStrength ~ Brand * Water, Towels2)

dox_scatterplot(Score~Major, Memory, color = Wordlist)
